WEBVTT

00:00.145 --> 00:01.753
Previously on
<i>The Client List...</i>

00:01.781 --> 00:03.301
Come on. Let's give daddy
his presents.

00:03.615 --> 00:04.482
I'll bring my gift
next time I come over.

00:04.516 --> 00:06.117
Didn't have time
to shop.

00:06.151 --> 00:07.918
What? You too busy to get
your big brother a present?

00:08.010 --> 00:09.578
The bank called again
about our mortgage.

00:09.612 --> 00:11.480
You and me, we're gonna
get through this together,

00:11.514 --> 00:12.581
like we always do,
right?

00:12.615 --> 00:13.315
Yeah.

00:13.349 --> 00:14.683
Kyle?

00:17.287 --> 00:20.222
Kyle left me, and I have no idea
if he's ever coming back.

00:20.256 --> 00:21.490
Kyle's been ne a while.

00:21.524 --> 00:23.425
It might be time
to let the house go.

00:24.015 --> 00:26.550
Their daddy's gone. I can't
take their house away, too.

00:26.585 --> 00:28.586
Riley Parks. We spoke
on the phone about the job.

00:28.620 --> 00:31.589
Oh, right. When would you
like to start?

00:31.623 --> 00:33.724
Hi, Hank.

00:33.758 --> 00:35.893
I don't want to be rude, but
the girls that don't give extras

00:35.927 --> 00:37.761
don't really do very well
here.

00:37.796 --> 00:40.097
90% of what we do here
is legit.

00:40.131 --> 00:42.166
I have a client list
for a few guys

00:42.200 --> 00:44.201
who like
a little something extra.

00:46.037 --> 00:48.072
What if I was interested in
something that weren't on the menu?

00:48.106 --> 00:49.406
What are you
looking for?

00:49.441 --> 00:52.176
The guy on your table
was a cop.

00:52.210 --> 00:53.244
[ Siren wails ]

00:53.278 --> 00:55.012
I know you...
from the spa.

00:55.046 --> 00:56.914
Next time we meet,
I might not be so nice.

00:56.948 --> 01:00.251
I'm not quite sure what I would
do without you around here.

01:00.285 --> 01:02.253
A guy can't step in
for his brother?

01:02.287 --> 01:03.420
I didn't think
I'd be doing it alone.

01:03.455 --> 01:04.888
You are not alone.

01:11.229 --> 01:12.563
[ Doorbell rings ]

01:14.900 --> 01:17.301
Oh, my God.
Kyle.

01:17.335 --> 01:19.503
Can I at least peek in
and see the kids?

01:21.473 --> 01:22.940
Where are we?

01:22.974 --> 01:24.808
We are in a good place.

01:24.843 --> 01:27.544
Kyle coming back
doesn't change anything.

01:27.579 --> 01:31.715
I want you
to run the spa.

01:31.750 --> 01:33.817
Georgia:
In that file cabinet,

01:33.852 --> 01:37.121
there's a little book
with some very big names in it.

01:37.155 --> 01:38.489
The client list?

01:46.498 --> 01:48.432
I heard
you were in trouble.

01:56.574 --> 01:58.909
[ Police radio chatter ]

01:58.934 --> 02:02.934
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Client List 2x01 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>'Till I Make It on My Own</font>
Original Air Date on March 10, 2013

02:02.935 --> 02:07.935
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00FF00">elderman</font> ==

02:08.853 --> 02:10.554
Are you in trouble?

02:12.023 --> 02:14.124
Riley,
are you in trouble?

02:16.061 --> 02:17.428
[ Car door closes ]

02:19.030 --> 02:21.598
I'm sorry.

02:22.901 --> 02:25.703
Kyle, I'm so sorry.

02:25.737 --> 02:27.271
What? What is it?

02:30.608 --> 02:31.875
What's going on?

02:32.944 --> 02:35.012
There's something
I need to tell you.

02:35.046 --> 02:36.246
[ Keys jingle ]

02:45.123 --> 02:47.224
Riley.

02:49.060 --> 02:50.094
Sorry about this.

02:51.796 --> 02:52.896
Me too.

02:56.434 --> 02:57.534
Kyle Parks,
you're under arrest.

02:57.569 --> 03:00.037
Hands behind your back.

03:00.071 --> 03:01.772
Let's go!
Hand's behind your back.

03:01.806 --> 03:04.375
[ Siren wails ]
Goodbye.

03:04.409 --> 03:06.243
[ Gasps ] Kyle.

03:07.746 --> 03:10.547
...can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

03:10.582 --> 03:12.549
Kyle, what the hell is going on?
You have the right to an attorney.

03:12.584 --> 03:14.418
Kyle, what did you do?!
If you cannot afford an attorney,

03:14.452 --> 03:15.573
one will be appointed
to you.

03:17.422 --> 03:19.089
[ Kyle sighs ]

03:19.124 --> 03:21.258
It's not
what you think.

03:22.460 --> 03:23.961
[ Grunts ]

03:25.196 --> 03:26.563
[ Car door closes ]

03:26.598 --> 03:28.265
[ Engine turns over,
siren wails ]

03:42.113 --> 03:43.847
[ Sirens wailing ]

03:49.821 --> 03:51.255
I'm here
to see Kyle Parks.

03:51.289 --> 03:52.589
Go to
the waiting room,

03:52.624 --> 03:54.358
and we'll call you
when we're ready.

03:55.126 --> 03:56.493
Wow. [ Sighs ]

03:56.528 --> 03:58.962
That is a beautiful family
that you've got there.

03:58.997 --> 04:01.832
You know, I bet if their daddy
was being booked for something,

04:01.866 --> 04:03.133
you'd want to be able
to tell them

04:03.168 --> 04:05.769
what he was being booked
for, right?

04:05.804 --> 04:07.604
Their daddy might be
in that picture,

04:07.639 --> 04:09.306
but he hasn't been
in mine in years.

04:09.340 --> 04:11.275
Good for you
for going it alone.

04:11.309 --> 04:14.845
My guy has been gone
for, you know, a year, and...

04:16.981 --> 04:19.116
Look, I really just need
something to tell my kids.

04:19.149 --> 04:20.617
The state of Texas

04:20.652 --> 04:22.786
does not allow me
to divulge any information

04:22.821 --> 04:25.789
till he is booked
and processed.

04:25.824 --> 04:27.891
Nice to know
some of them come back.

04:34.365 --> 04:36.333
Thank you.

04:39.671 --> 04:43.340
[ Cellphone rings, buzzes ]

04:43.374 --> 04:44.641
Hey, mama. It's me.

04:44.676 --> 04:45.909
Sweetie, what's wrong?

04:45.944 --> 04:47.578
Is everything all right?
Oh, yeah.

04:47.612 --> 04:49.012
Yeah, I'm -- I'm fine.

04:49.047 --> 04:50.647
Um...

04:50.682 --> 04:52.816
I'm at
the county jail.

04:52.851 --> 04:54.184
Uh, it's Kyle --

04:54.219 --> 04:55.819
I think he's in some sort
of trouble.

04:55.854 --> 04:58.422
That man is nothing but trouble.
What's he done this time?

04:58.456 --> 05:00.591
Honestly, I don't even know
what to think.

05:00.625 --> 05:02.025
Look, you may have to
take the kids

05:02.060 --> 05:03.193
to school
tomorrow morning.

05:03.228 --> 05:04.428
Sure thing.

05:04.462 --> 05:06.130
And whatever's going on
with Kyle,

05:06.164 --> 05:07.498
remember
what I always say.

05:07.532 --> 05:09.399
I know, mama.
[ Chuckles ]

05:09.434 --> 05:11.135
"Husbands
are like pancakes.

05:11.169 --> 05:12.803
There's no shame
in throwing the first one out."

05:12.837 --> 05:15.339
And I should know.
I've had my share of pancakes.

05:16.374 --> 05:17.841
Okay, bye.

05:17.876 --> 05:19.009
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:34.025 --> 05:35.626
Riley.

05:37.028 --> 05:37.995
Riley.

05:38.029 --> 05:39.329
[ Gasps ]

05:39.364 --> 05:40.531
[ Evan chuckles ]

05:40.565 --> 05:41.832
Hey, there,
sleeping beauty.

05:41.866 --> 05:43.500
I come
bearing doughnuts.

05:43.535 --> 05:44.835
[ Sighs ]

05:44.869 --> 05:46.370
I'm sorry.
I must have dozed off.

05:46.404 --> 05:47.704
How long
have you been here?

05:47.739 --> 05:49.673
Oh, not long.
I just got here.

05:49.707 --> 05:51.942
You know how it is
at your house. [ Chuckles ]

05:51.976 --> 05:53.610
Linette called Lacey.
Lacey told Dale.

05:53.645 --> 05:55.679
[ Sighs ]
Dale called me.

05:55.713 --> 05:58.949
Please, tell me this is all
some kind of misunderstanding.

05:58.983 --> 06:00.717
[ Sighs ]
That's what I'm hoping.

06:02.253 --> 06:03.854
I got you
jelly-filled.

06:03.888 --> 06:05.689
Cream, one sugar.

06:05.723 --> 06:07.524
[ Sighs ]
Oh, and if you're gonna fall asleep

06:07.559 --> 06:08.959
on a police-department
bench,

06:08.993 --> 06:10.727
you should take better care
of your purse.

06:11.930 --> 06:13.897
Diary's
gonna fall out.

06:13.932 --> 06:15.365
Oh, you know what?

06:15.400 --> 06:17.734
That's just some
accounting stuff from work.

06:19.404 --> 06:21.572
You didn't have to
come down here so late.

06:21.606 --> 06:25.242
Any excuse for an apple fritter
and a cup of lukewarm coffee.

06:25.276 --> 06:26.376
[ Chuckles ]

06:26.411 --> 06:27.477
You holding up okay?

06:27.512 --> 06:29.346
Better
now that you're here.

06:30.682 --> 06:31.982
Listen...

06:32.016 --> 06:33.684
No matter what's going on
with Kyle,

06:33.718 --> 06:35.819
it doesn't
change my feelings.

06:36.888 --> 06:37.888
Me, too.

06:37.922 --> 06:39.957
Hal: Mrs. Parks?

06:39.991 --> 06:41.191
That's me.

06:41.226 --> 06:42.359
[ Sighs ] Howdy.

06:42.393 --> 06:43.560
I'm, uh,
Hal Burkett,

06:43.595 --> 06:45.696
your husband's
public defender.

06:45.730 --> 06:47.698
Whew. Got his file
right here.

06:47.732 --> 06:49.533
Parks, Kevin.

06:49.567 --> 06:51.068
Kyle.
Oh.

06:51.102 --> 06:52.869
All right. [ Sighs ]
Here we go.

06:52.904 --> 06:53.870
Oh. Thank you.

06:53.905 --> 06:56.373
[ Sighs ] Whew.

06:56.407 --> 06:58.208
Felony theft.
[ Sighs ]

06:58.243 --> 06:59.543
Uh, your hubby --

06:59.577 --> 07:02.479
uh...can we, uh, talk
in front of this guy?

07:02.513 --> 07:04.248
Yeah, he's his brother.

07:04.282 --> 07:06.416
All right. [ Sighs ]
Your, uh...

07:06.451 --> 07:09.920
Your husband allegedly stole
a semi truck full of copper wire

07:09.954 --> 07:11.421
from a company
he was employed by.

07:11.456 --> 07:12.556
Well,
that can't be true.

07:12.590 --> 07:14.825
Like I said,
"allegedly."

07:14.859 --> 07:17.394
Okay. Why would someone
steal copper wire?

07:17.428 --> 07:18.855
It happens all the time
on my construction sites.

07:18.880 --> 07:20.097
[ Cellphone buzzes, beeps ]

07:20.098 --> 07:21.498
It's worth thousands
on the black market,

07:21.532 --> 07:22.833
but...my brother?

07:22.867 --> 07:24.401
Yeah, I mean,
he's a lot of things,

07:24.435 --> 07:26.270
but he's not
a...thief.

07:26.304 --> 07:27.738
[ Cellphone buttons clicking ]
Well, good news is,

07:27.772 --> 07:28.905
you know,
it's just one charge.

07:28.940 --> 07:30.061
If your husband
pleads out --

07:31.042 --> 07:32.409
that means "guilty,"
by the way --

07:32.443 --> 07:33.844
we're not looking
at that much time --

07:33.878 --> 07:35.112
a couple of years.
[ Clicking continues ]

07:35.146 --> 07:36.413
You haven't
even talked to him.

07:36.447 --> 07:37.748
I mean, what if
he isn't guilty?

07:37.782 --> 07:38.749
[ Laughs ]

07:38.783 --> 07:40.083
Uh, look, like I said,

07:40.118 --> 07:41.418
it'll go a lot smoother
for Kevin --

07:41.452 --> 07:42.586
Kyle.

07:42.620 --> 07:44.187
Uh, Kyle, right.

07:44.222 --> 07:47.024
Mrs. Parks, I've fixed it
so you can see your husband now.

07:47.058 --> 07:48.925
[ Sighs ] Thank you.

07:48.960 --> 07:50.761
Do you want me
to go with you?

07:50.795 --> 07:53.275
No, that's the last thing I need
is you two in a room together.

07:53.965 --> 07:55.265
Hey.

07:55.300 --> 07:56.433
Kyle.

07:56.467 --> 07:57.534
Yes, ma'am.

07:57.568 --> 07:59.236
Sorry.

08:02.140 --> 08:03.940
Why are you here,
mee maw?

08:03.975 --> 08:05.776
Yeah, where's mommy?

08:05.810 --> 08:07.944
She had to do some mommy errands,
but she'll be back real soon.

08:07.979 --> 08:09.179
Don't you worry, sweetheart.

08:09.213 --> 08:10.781
But mommy said
she was gonna help me

08:10.815 --> 08:12.282
"prehearse"
for the science fair.

08:12.317 --> 08:14.551
I can help you "prehearse."

08:14.585 --> 08:15.952
I'm all ears.

08:15.987 --> 08:18.322
Now, go on, honey.
Go get your report.

08:18.356 --> 08:20.657
Is daddy coming
to the science fair tonight?

08:21.859 --> 08:23.493
We'll have to see about that.

08:25.430 --> 08:28.131
Kyle, I can't help you
without the truth.

08:28.166 --> 08:30.634
Just...what did you do?
[ Sighs ]

08:30.668 --> 08:32.469
The truth or I walk.

08:32.503 --> 08:34.337
Look,
when I got clean...

08:34.371 --> 08:37.174
I couldn't come back to you
and the kids empty-handed.

08:38.710 --> 08:41.611
The kids wanted you to show up.
They don't care about money.

08:41.645 --> 08:43.212
Yeah, but I do.

08:43.246 --> 08:45.282
I care about providing.

08:45.316 --> 08:46.950
I care about
being a man.

08:46.984 --> 08:49.619
So, you stole.
From crooks.

08:49.654 --> 08:52.622
That construction company
is run by a bunch of thieves.

08:52.657 --> 08:55.292
And you're different
because...

08:55.326 --> 08:56.493
[ Sighs softly ]

08:56.527 --> 08:57.994
Well,
I guess I'm not.

09:00.665 --> 09:02.599
Look, I know
I did a bad thing.

09:03.701 --> 09:06.370
All right, but that money
waz for you and the kids.

09:07.505 --> 09:10.173
Come on. Haven't you ever done
a bad thing for a good reason?

09:12.443 --> 09:15.545
Now, I think that I may
have a way out of all this.

09:16.781 --> 09:18.181
But I need you
to do me one favor.

09:20.184 --> 09:22.686
Don't give up on me.

09:26.858 --> 09:29.593
I never gave up
on you, Kyle.

09:29.627 --> 09:31.862
You gave up on us.

09:48.242 --> 09:49.308
Riley: I know, mama.

09:49.343 --> 09:50.877
I will be there.

09:50.911 --> 09:52.078
Just take the kids
to school, okay?

09:52.112 --> 09:53.813
I just need
to let my head...

09:53.847 --> 09:56.315
I don't know,
get straight for a minute.

09:56.350 --> 09:57.550
Linette: I'll get
the kids ready.

09:57.584 --> 09:58.985
Thank you.

09:59.019 --> 10:02.755
♪ I don't want
to be left behind ♪

10:02.790 --> 10:05.892
♪ Distance was a friend
of mine ♪

10:05.926 --> 10:09.395
♪ Catching breath
in a web of lies ♪

10:09.430 --> 10:14.767
♪ I've spent most of my time

10:14.802 --> 10:18.271
♪ catching my breath,
letting it go ♪

10:18.305 --> 10:22.408
♪ turning my cheek
for the sake of the show ♪

10:22.443 --> 10:25.812
♪ now that you know
this is my life ♪

10:25.846 --> 10:30.416
♪ I won't be told
what's supposed to be right ♪

10:31.418 --> 10:33.386
♪ catch my breath

10:33.420 --> 10:35.421
♪ won't let them get me down

10:35.456 --> 10:37.390
♪ it's all so simple now

10:37.424 --> 10:40.927
♪ addicted to the love I found

10:40.961 --> 10:44.397
♪ heavy heart
now a weightless cloud ♪

10:44.431 --> 10:46.065
[ Door handle rattling ]

10:46.099 --> 10:48.935
No! Are you kidding me?!
[ Sighs ]

10:48.969 --> 10:53.906
♪ I'll spend
the rest of my time ♪

10:53.941 --> 10:54.742
♪ catching my breath

10:56.643 --> 10:58.277
♪ no, I can't hold it back

10:58.312 --> 11:00.246
♪ I ain't got time for that

11:00.280 --> 11:01.414
♪ catch my breath

11:03.050 --> 11:04.183
♪ catch my breath

11:04.218 --> 11:06.352
♪ won't let them get me down

11:06.386 --> 11:09.355
[ toys rattle ]

11:09.389 --> 11:10.656
Mama!

11:10.691 --> 11:12.191
I need to take the kids
to school.

11:12.226 --> 11:13.259
Can I borrow your car?

11:13.293 --> 11:14.861
What's happened to yours?

11:14.895 --> 11:16.529
Riley, are you okay?

11:16.563 --> 11:17.630
Travis: Mom!

11:18.465 --> 11:20.366
Katie: Mommy!
Hey! Hi.

11:20.400 --> 11:21.968
Mommy!
Hi.

11:22.002 --> 11:23.269
I don't suppose
this is the best time

11:23.303 --> 11:24.470
to tell me
what's what.

11:24.505 --> 11:26.105
Now is certainly not
the best time.

11:26.139 --> 11:27.607
Okay. Mama's gonna
take y'all to school.

11:27.641 --> 11:28.774
Can daddy
pick us up?

11:28.809 --> 11:30.042
Uh...

11:30.077 --> 11:31.444
Not today.

11:31.478 --> 11:33.112
Will he be here
tonight?

11:33.146 --> 11:34.447
We're gonna talk
about that later, okay?

11:34.481 --> 11:35.721
So, go on.
Get in mee maw's car.

11:37.184 --> 11:39.151
So, how bad is it,
on a scale from 1 to 10?

11:40.654 --> 11:42.288
[ Clicks tongue ]

11:42.322 --> 11:44.290
I smashed
my own car window.

11:44.324 --> 11:45.725
Calling that an 11.

11:45.759 --> 11:47.660
Are you going back
to see him?

11:47.694 --> 11:50.296
No. I'm gonna drop the kids off
and then go to work.

11:50.330 --> 11:52.932
Our family has been just fine
without him for a year.

11:52.966 --> 11:55.101
Mama, he left me
without even a phone call.

11:55.135 --> 11:56.135
[ Sighs ]

11:56.169 --> 11:57.603
He may be locked up,

11:57.638 --> 12:00.806
but...at least this time
I know where he is.

12:03.677 --> 12:07.113
[ Train whistle blowing ]

12:07.147 --> 12:09.949
Woman: Ladies, all hairdressers
on deck, please.

12:09.983 --> 12:13.452
As of today, the Curl Up and Dry
is switching to a brand-new

12:13.487 --> 12:15.588
and very, very exciting
business model.

12:15.622 --> 12:17.423
[ Quietly ]
Which is guaranteed to suck.

12:17.457 --> 12:20.593
Each of you gets
to rent your very own chair,

12:20.627 --> 12:22.261
be your own boss,
make your own hours.

12:22.296 --> 12:23.429
Pay our own salary?

12:23.463 --> 12:25.064
Yes. Oh,
and health insurance,

12:25.098 --> 12:26.899
but the upside's unlimited.

12:26.934 --> 12:27.900
You're right.
This sucks.

12:27.935 --> 12:29.302
No, I was wrong.

12:29.336 --> 12:31.404
My friend Raylene's salon
runs this way,

12:31.438 --> 12:32.905
and she makes
way more money than us.

12:32.940 --> 12:34.407
We could save up.

12:34.441 --> 12:36.275
You always wanted
to open your own place.

12:36.310 --> 12:38.077
I'm sticking with, "this sucks."
Reporter: In local news,

12:38.111 --> 12:40.079
former U.T. starting
quarterback Kyle Parks

12:40.113 --> 12:42.281
was arrested last night...
Not as much as that does.

12:42.316 --> 12:43.916
...on suspicion
of robbing Houston's

12:43.951 --> 12:45.585
Vandermeyer
Construction company.

12:45.619 --> 12:47.920
Parks faces charges
for the alleged theft

12:47.955 --> 12:50.289
of a semi truck
loaded with copper wire.

12:50.324 --> 12:52.758
Parks is being held
by Harris county authorities,

12:52.793 --> 12:54.527
where he will be arraigned
later this week.

12:54.561 --> 12:57.597
If convicted, he faces
up to 10 years in prison.

12:57.631 --> 12:59.432
Parks dominated...
[ Horn honks ]

12:59.466 --> 13:01.100
Male reporter:
Kyle Parks, local football hero

13:01.134 --> 13:03.302
is being held
by Harris county authorities

13:03.337 --> 13:05.371
and will be arraigned
later this week.

13:05.405 --> 13:07.940
If convicted,
Parks faces up to 10 years

13:07.975 --> 13:09.942
in the state penitentiary.

13:09.977 --> 13:11.544
Female reporter #2:
...Filled with copper wire

13:11.578 --> 13:13.446
from Houston's
Vandermeyer Construction.

13:13.480 --> 13:16.449
Kyle Parks, a Beaumont native,
has fallen far

13:16.483 --> 13:19.785
from his high-soaring days
as U.T.'s starting quarterback.

13:19.820 --> 13:21.654
Mr. Parks
was arrested last night

13:21.688 --> 13:23.723
and is being held
at Harris County jail.

13:23.757 --> 13:26.626
The investigation is ongoing
as police continue --

13:26.660 --> 13:27.860
[ TV turns off ]

13:29.363 --> 13:31.164
Well, if y'all have come
for a surprise party,

13:31.198 --> 13:32.498
you are six months
too late,

13:32.532 --> 13:33.966
and I hope
you brought me some cake.

13:34.001 --> 13:35.301
Sweetie,
I know change is hard.

13:35.335 --> 13:36.736
Mama, I really
don't want to hear it.

13:36.770 --> 13:38.771
The Curl is using
a chair-rental system.

13:38.805 --> 13:41.440
Do I like it?
Not one little bit,

13:41.475 --> 13:43.442
but I have to face the reality
of the situation.

13:43.477 --> 13:46.479
I have made my decision,
and I'm hiring an attorney.

13:46.513 --> 13:49.415
Well, thank the lord.
If you haven't found one yet,

13:49.449 --> 13:51.283
the guy who handled
my fourth divorce was great.

13:51.318 --> 13:54.020
I am hiring Kyle
a criminal defense attorney.

13:54.054 --> 13:57.923
Riley, you are not bailing
that man out of trouble.

13:57.958 --> 14:00.259
I have to do something.
He's the father of my kids.

14:00.293 --> 14:01.961
You can't afford
to pay some fancy lawyer.

14:01.995 --> 14:03.929
You two should have
seen this public defender.

14:03.964 --> 14:05.464
He couldn't even
zip up his own fly,

14:05.499 --> 14:06.966
let alone
help Kyle win his case.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.602
After all he's done,
it shouldn't be on you.

14:09.636 --> 14:11.804
Lacey's right.
This is Kyle's mess, not yours.

14:11.838 --> 14:13.739
I appreciate the input.

14:14.574 --> 14:16.442
Actually, no.

14:16.476 --> 14:17.777
[ Claps hands ]
No, I don't.

14:17.811 --> 14:19.645
You know what?
End of discussion.

14:20.814 --> 14:22.254
Lacey, we've got to
get back to work.

14:22.282 --> 14:24.016
I'm waiting
in your car.

14:24.051 --> 14:26.318
I'm not gonna stand around
watching her make a mistake.

14:28.388 --> 14:30.022
[ Door slams ]
Well, that went well.

14:30.057 --> 14:32.291
So, you gonna
stay mad at me, too?

14:32.325 --> 14:35.428
Riley, none of us
are mad at you.

14:35.462 --> 14:36.862
We're worried...

14:36.897 --> 14:39.098
and angry -- at Kyle.
[ Sighs ]

14:39.132 --> 14:40.266
I can't stand
seeing him

14:40.300 --> 14:41.967
treat you and the kids
like this...

14:42.002 --> 14:45.871
Especially
when you have better options.

14:45.906 --> 14:48.607
Did I tell you
that Evan showed up

14:48.642 --> 14:50.009
at the police station
last night,

14:50.043 --> 14:52.144
and he brought doughnuts?
Jelly-filled?

14:52.179 --> 14:53.979
Raspberry
and powdered sugar.

14:54.014 --> 14:55.381
My favorite.

14:55.415 --> 14:57.216
Oh, and yours.

14:57.250 --> 14:58.617
Evan's a great guy.

14:58.652 --> 15:00.152
He's been there for you

15:00.187 --> 15:02.455
while Kyle's been out
holding up copper trucks.

15:02.489 --> 15:04.657
Kyle did something illegal
to help his family.

15:04.691 --> 15:06.492
I mean, how can I judge him
for that?

15:06.526 --> 15:07.960
That is different.

15:07.994 --> 15:10.129
No. We're both
breaking the law.

15:10.163 --> 15:12.131
What you do at the Rub
might be illegal,

15:12.165 --> 15:14.166
but you do not steal.

15:14.201 --> 15:15.634
Those men...want you.

15:15.669 --> 15:17.503
It's not like you're reaching
in their pockets

15:17.537 --> 15:18.838
and grabbing
what's in there.

15:18.872 --> 15:21.707
Not unless
it'll get me a bigger tip.

15:23.176 --> 15:25.344
Lacey, I'm kidding.

15:26.613 --> 15:28.314
[ Laughs ]

15:28.348 --> 15:30.416
Now, will you just
do me a favor, please,

15:30.450 --> 15:32.685
and have my back
on this?

15:32.719 --> 15:34.487
I always do.

15:34.521 --> 15:36.655
I know. You're so good
that way. [ Laughs ]

15:36.690 --> 15:38.758
[ Door opens ]
Evan: Riley.

15:38.792 --> 15:40.693
You should go.
[ Clears throat ] Okay.

15:41.862 --> 15:43.095
Guess you heard
the news.

15:43.130 --> 15:44.363
Oh, yeah. I heard.

15:44.397 --> 15:45.531
[ Sighs ]

15:45.565 --> 15:47.566
Just...
Tell me one thing.

15:48.735 --> 15:49.802
Did he do it?

15:51.638 --> 15:53.606
[ Scoffs ]
[ Clears throat ]

15:53.640 --> 15:55.741
Well, at least this time
it's not your problem.

15:57.644 --> 15:59.645
I'm hiring Kyle
an attorney.

15:59.679 --> 16:02.014
You can't afford that,
Riley,

16:02.048 --> 16:04.083
and why are you
standing by him?

16:04.117 --> 16:05.751
Because he is...

16:05.786 --> 16:08.921
Katie and Travis' daddy,
all right?

16:08.955 --> 16:11.090
And you saw
that idiot public defender.

16:11.124 --> 16:14.527
Are you sure you're doing this
for the kids and not you?

16:14.561 --> 16:15.861
Evan...

16:15.896 --> 16:18.197
I meant what I said
to you about us.

16:18.231 --> 16:19.732
It's just...

16:21.701 --> 16:23.369
[ Sighs ]

16:23.403 --> 16:25.204
I wish
we could be...

16:25.238 --> 16:27.439
selfish.

16:27.474 --> 16:29.041
Me, too.

16:30.744 --> 16:33.179
Well, can I at least see you
after work tonight?

16:33.213 --> 16:34.880
I have to meet
Kyle's attorney.

16:34.915 --> 16:36.849
I thought you said

16:36.883 --> 16:38.784
you weren't gonna let
Kyle's problems get in our way.

16:38.819 --> 16:40.686
Hey.

16:40.720 --> 16:43.789
Now, I'm gonna call you
when I get home tonight, okay?

16:43.824 --> 16:46.392
Now, I promise.

16:47.661 --> 16:49.061
Promise.

16:50.397 --> 16:51.430
Come on.

16:51.464 --> 16:54.400
Walk a girl
to her car?

17:00.841 --> 17:02.308
High and dry.

17:02.342 --> 17:04.108
Now we got clients
coming out of our asses.

17:04.144 --> 17:05.911
[ Sighs ] I can't believe that
Jolene and Kendra just quit.

17:05.945 --> 17:07.213
And Dee Ann
hurt her knee at zumba.

17:07.247 --> 17:08.646
[ Sighs ]
Riley...

17:08.682 --> 17:09.848
We safe?

17:11.451 --> 17:13.886
Yes. Yes, of course.
We are safe.

17:13.920 --> 17:15.554
Unfortunately,
we have to stick together.

17:15.589 --> 17:17.723
What about the police, huh?
They coming back here?

17:17.757 --> 17:20.392
No, that had nothing to do with
the Rub and everything to do --

17:20.426 --> 17:21.587
Georgia:
Your no-good husband?

17:23.630 --> 17:25.497
[ Sighs deeply ]
Georgia, you're back.

17:25.531 --> 17:27.465
And not a moment too soon.

17:32.830 --> 17:35.298
[ Both laugh ]

17:35.332 --> 17:37.133
Riley and I need to have
a meeting of the minds.

17:37.167 --> 17:39.101
Selena,
tell the clients

17:39.136 --> 17:41.204
that they'll be comped
a free massage for their patience.

17:41.238 --> 17:44.040
Oh, great. Two-for-one.
Good thinking.

17:44.074 --> 17:46.108
'Cause that's really
gonna help our schedule.

17:46.143 --> 17:49.812
Still a smartass, I see.
[ Sighs ]

17:49.847 --> 17:51.314
And a pain
in one, too.

17:51.348 --> 17:54.784
[ Chuckles ]
Some things never change.

17:54.818 --> 17:55.885
[ Sighs ]

17:55.919 --> 17:57.520
Riley,
are you all right?

17:58.755 --> 18:00.823
I saw the news
about Kyle.

18:00.858 --> 18:03.292
Oh, I'm --

18:03.327 --> 18:05.161
I'm hanging in there.
[ Laughs ]

18:05.195 --> 18:06.796
Well, if there's anything
you need --

18:06.830 --> 18:07.964
Thank you.

18:07.998 --> 18:09.131
I'm just glad
that you're back.

18:09.166 --> 18:11.133
You know,
I was worried.

18:11.168 --> 18:13.336
I mean, you just dropped off
the face of the earth like that.

18:13.370 --> 18:15.071
I'm fine.
I just had to lay low

18:15.105 --> 18:17.406
once that councilman
gave us heat.

18:17.441 --> 18:19.642
Well, we did not hear one word
from that man after you left.

18:19.676 --> 18:21.210
You're damn right.

18:21.245 --> 18:23.646
I called in a favor from one
of my very powerful clients,

18:23.680 --> 18:25.982
but I knew it was best
for everyone

18:26.016 --> 18:27.516
if I just
stayed away.

18:27.551 --> 18:29.151
But you're back
for good now, right?

18:29.186 --> 18:30.486
[ Sighs ]
Well, about that --

18:30.520 --> 18:32.154
[ chuckling ]
I've got a situation.

18:32.189 --> 18:33.155
What do you mean?

18:33.190 --> 18:34.657
There's this gentleman.

18:34.691 --> 18:36.359
[ Gasps ]

18:36.393 --> 18:39.862
Georgia, you met someone?
Who is he? What's his name?

18:39.897 --> 18:41.831
His name is Harold.

18:41.865 --> 18:43.866
He's been on the back burner
for a few months,

18:43.901 --> 18:46.035
but I must say
that while I was away,

18:46.069 --> 18:47.937
our pots did boil over.
Oh!

18:47.971 --> 18:50.539
[ Both laugh ]
That's great.

18:50.574 --> 18:52.375
Oh,
look at that smile.

18:52.409 --> 18:54.277
I'm happy for you.

18:54.311 --> 18:55.878
Oh, me, too, honey.
Me, too.

18:55.913 --> 18:58.014
So, what does
this relationship

18:58.048 --> 18:59.849
have to do with
you coming back to the Rub?

18:59.883 --> 19:01.450
Well,
Harold is a good man.

19:01.485 --> 19:03.853
I don't want to have to keep
lying to him about what I do.

19:03.887 --> 19:06.389
Georgia, this --
this place is your life.

19:06.423 --> 19:09.392
And it cost me
my first husband.

19:09.426 --> 19:13.062
I never want to go through
that kind of pain again.

19:13.096 --> 19:16.666
Harold could be
my last chance at love.

19:18.001 --> 19:19.135
So, what are you
gonna do?

19:19.169 --> 19:20.436
The truth?

19:21.672 --> 19:23.039
I don't know...

19:23.073 --> 19:24.407
But until
I figure it out,

19:24.441 --> 19:27.176
I want you to keep doing
what you're doing.

19:29.246 --> 19:30.746
[ Sighs ] Okay.

19:30.781 --> 19:32.048
[ Chuckles softly ]

19:32.082 --> 19:33.983
Okay.
So, here's the plan.

19:34.017 --> 19:35.484
We're gonna split
Kendra's clients.

19:35.519 --> 19:37.286
You'll take Dee Ann's,
and I'll do Jolene's,

19:37.321 --> 19:39.388
'cause we both know that you
don't want to do a legit massage.

19:39.423 --> 19:41.057
All right, if you're gonna
get all high and mighty

19:41.091 --> 19:42.558
about the kind of massages
we do, save it --

19:42.592 --> 19:43.993
been there, heard that.
Yeah.

19:44.027 --> 19:45.728
You wouldn't believe
the things I've heard

19:45.762 --> 19:47.863
coming from your massages.
Oh, and there you go

19:47.898 --> 19:49.102
with your little judge-y,
pageant-queen face.

19:49.127 --> 19:50.666
Okay,
here's the new deal.

19:50.667 --> 19:52.201
Whatever you and the client
decide in that room

19:52.235 --> 19:53.369
is cool with me.

19:53.403 --> 19:54.804
The room
becomes like Vegas.

19:54.838 --> 19:56.505
Whatever happens in there
stays in there.

19:57.908 --> 20:00.076
And no, uh...

20:00.110 --> 20:01.911
Judge-y, pageant-queen face
from you?

20:01.945 --> 20:03.846
And no stink face
from you?

20:05.449 --> 20:07.049
You clear this
with Georgia?

20:07.084 --> 20:08.384
Absolutely.
She's on board.

20:08.418 --> 20:09.919
Really?

20:11.421 --> 20:12.488
I'm gonna make
so much more money

20:12.522 --> 20:14.290
than anyone
in this place.

20:14.324 --> 20:16.559
Yeah, I really think that you're
gonna blow the clients away --

20:16.593 --> 20:17.827
pun intended.

20:17.861 --> 20:19.395
[ Chuckles ]

20:19.429 --> 20:20.930
You know, I think
this is the first time

20:20.964 --> 20:22.832
I've kind of liked you
since you started working here.

20:22.866 --> 20:24.400
Speaking of work --
today's schedule --

20:24.434 --> 20:26.168
you're gonna need something
to write this down.

20:26.203 --> 20:27.603
You got a pen?
No, I got my phone, though.

20:27.637 --> 20:29.238
Okay, you got Nelson
at 10:30.

20:29.272 --> 20:30.906
He's got a comb-over,
so don't mess with his hair,

20:30.941 --> 20:32.241
and I hope you brought
your pom-poms

20:32.275 --> 20:34.276
because he loves himself
a cheerleader.

20:34.311 --> 20:35.611
Sergio's at 11:45.

20:35.645 --> 20:36.946
Oh, look at you.

20:36.980 --> 20:39.015
You got a "pornographic"
memory. [ Chuckles ]

20:39.049 --> 20:40.683
So, who's first at bat
for you?

20:40.717 --> 20:42.597
Oh, you know that guy
they call "Mr. Louboutin"?

20:43.487 --> 20:45.755
Yeah, are you kidding me?
So, what?

20:45.789 --> 20:47.757
Just because you're in charge
of this place now,

20:47.791 --> 20:49.091
you get to pick
the best clients?

20:49.126 --> 20:50.092
Well...

20:50.127 --> 20:51.961
If the shoe fits.

20:51.995 --> 20:55.798
[ Sighs ]
Those are not just shoes.

20:55.832 --> 20:58.100
They are a work
of art.

20:58.135 --> 20:59.535
Beautiful shoes
for a beautiful woman.

20:59.569 --> 21:00.870
You know what?

21:00.904 --> 21:02.438
Shoes and flattery
do get you everywhere.

21:02.472 --> 21:04.140
[ Laughs ]

21:04.174 --> 21:06.976
You know, I was real sorry
to hear Kendra up and quit,

21:07.010 --> 21:09.779
but...I think you and I
are gonna get along just fine.

21:09.813 --> 21:12.715
Really, now?
What'd you have in mind?

21:12.749 --> 21:15.718
She used to take a stroll
up and down my back.

21:15.752 --> 21:18.287
Really?
Kendra did that?

21:18.321 --> 21:19.455
Mm-hmm.

21:19.489 --> 21:21.390
That's a first.
[ Chuckles ]

21:21.425 --> 21:22.892
Look, I promise...

21:22.926 --> 21:24.794
I'll have you smiling
by the time you leave here.

21:24.828 --> 21:26.162
[ Chuckles ]

21:26.196 --> 21:27.963
[ ZZ Ward's
"Out the Gun Down" plays ]

21:27.998 --> 21:29.632
♪ Adeline, have mercy

21:29.666 --> 21:31.634
♪ you don't want to break my heart ♪
Like this?

21:31.668 --> 21:34.236
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

21:34.271 --> 21:36.305
Exactly like that.
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh

21:36.339 --> 21:37.339
♪ put the gun down

21:37.374 --> 21:39.075
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh

21:39.109 --> 21:40.643
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh

21:40.677 --> 21:42.678
♪ put the gun down

21:44.514 --> 21:46.582
Mrs. Parks.

21:46.616 --> 21:48.484
[ Laughs ]
Thanks for meeting me here.

21:48.518 --> 21:50.119
I'm due in court
in 10 minutes. [ Sighs ]

21:50.153 --> 21:52.054
Did you have a chance
to go over Kyle's case?

21:52.089 --> 21:55.458
I reviewed your husband's case.
He has no priors, correct?

21:55.492 --> 21:56.992
No, not even
a speeding ticket.

21:57.027 --> 21:58.461
In other words,
other than this...

21:58.495 --> 22:00.563
misunderstanding
with his employer,

22:00.597 --> 22:02.731
Kyle's an exceptional
husband and father.

22:02.766 --> 22:03.999
Yes.

22:04.034 --> 22:05.835
Sure.

22:06.870 --> 22:08.971
Well, uh...
based on my experience,

22:09.005 --> 22:10.639
given that
he has no priors

22:10.674 --> 22:13.809
and...if the missing
semi truck full of copper

22:13.844 --> 22:16.078
were to mysteriously turn up
on the streets of Laredo

22:16.113 --> 22:17.847
or any old place...

22:17.881 --> 22:19.849
I'd say Kyle has a good chance
of beating these charges.

22:19.883 --> 22:20.950
[ Sighs ]

22:21.885 --> 22:24.820
All we need is a retainer
of $5,000 to get started.

22:24.855 --> 22:27.823
$5,000 -- up front?

22:27.858 --> 22:29.325
Well, that's
how retainers work.

22:29.359 --> 22:31.961
[ Sighs ] Well, I don't have
that kind of cash on me.

22:33.230 --> 22:34.663
Cash. [ Laughs ]

22:34.698 --> 22:37.833
Uh...only my criminal
clients pay cash,

22:37.868 --> 22:40.069
and you don't look like
a criminal to me, Mrs. Parks.

22:41.571 --> 22:43.539
I'll get you your money.
[ Sighs ]

22:43.573 --> 22:45.875
Won't leave you high and dry.
[ Chuckles ]

22:48.044 --> 22:49.945
Travis,
your intestines look great,

22:49.980 --> 22:52.715
but the science fair's
in half an hour. We got to go.

22:52.749 --> 22:54.517
But daddy's
not here yet.

22:54.551 --> 22:55.885
Why hasn't he come home?

22:57.254 --> 22:59.522
Uh, he ran into
a little bit of trouble...

22:59.556 --> 23:01.357
on his construction site,
you know?

23:01.391 --> 23:03.392
So, he may not be home
for a while.

23:03.426 --> 23:05.694
Is he ever
coming back?

23:05.729 --> 23:07.363
Yes.

23:07.397 --> 23:10.466
He will.
I just don't know when.

23:10.500 --> 23:12.868
Tell you what -- why don't I
record the science fair,

23:12.903 --> 23:15.237
and we'll send it to your daddy
so it's like he's there, okay?

23:15.272 --> 23:16.739
Okay...

23:16.773 --> 23:18.974
But I still wish
he was coming with us.

23:19.009 --> 23:22.244
I know you do, baby.
I know.

23:22.279 --> 23:24.046
Now, come on,
you worked so hard.

23:24.080 --> 23:25.548
You don't want to miss it.
Let's go.

23:25.582 --> 23:26.916
Careful.
Oh, those are intestines.

23:29.519 --> 23:32.555
Hello.
I'm your amazing intestines.

23:32.589 --> 23:35.057
I'm an organ
just below your stomach.

23:35.091 --> 23:39.795
If you stretch me out,
I am 20 -- 52 -- 25 feet long.

23:40.764 --> 23:42.231
Thank you.

23:42.265 --> 23:43.599
[ Applause ]

23:48.205 --> 23:49.939
[ Indistinct conversation ]

23:52.309 --> 23:53.676
Ignore them.

23:53.710 --> 23:55.678
Biggest bunch of gossips
I've ever met.

23:55.712 --> 23:57.613
[ Chuckling ] They need to
mind their own bake sale.

23:57.647 --> 23:58.948
Karina.

23:58.982 --> 24:00.349
Our sons were
in kindergarten together.

24:00.383 --> 24:01.650
Ethan. He's adorable.

24:01.685 --> 24:03.619
You work at my bank?
Accounts manager.

24:03.653 --> 24:06.088
I handle your home loan
and the PTA treasury.

24:06.122 --> 24:08.090
I'm sorry about them.
No, it's all right.

24:08.124 --> 24:09.592
Small town --
nothing's more interesting

24:09.626 --> 24:11.360
than a fallen
beauty queen.

24:11.394 --> 24:13.796
[ Chuckles ] Well, my son
did his project on volcanoes.

24:13.830 --> 24:15.764
Maybe we can toss a few
of them in there.

24:15.799 --> 24:18.434
[ Laughs ] I think the universe
is gonna take care of them.

24:18.468 --> 24:20.069
[ Chuckles ]

24:26.743 --> 24:30.446
Hey, mommy.
Can I have a cupcake?

24:30.480 --> 24:31.447
Uh...

24:31.481 --> 24:33.449
Sure, baby.

24:33.483 --> 24:35.150
Um...here you go.

24:38.855 --> 24:40.656
[ Sighs ]

24:49.866 --> 24:52.835
Riley Parks. Detective Monroe.
We need a word.

24:54.871 --> 24:56.705
Detective Dunbar,
Houston P.D.

24:58.041 --> 25:00.276
You know,
Nathan says to say hi.

25:01.344 --> 25:05.147
Riley. I'm really sorry
to bother you at Travis' school.

25:05.181 --> 25:08.317
I'm so sorry,
but do I know you?

25:08.351 --> 25:09.752
Oh, you probably
don't recognize me

25:09.786 --> 25:11.654
without my helmet on.

25:11.688 --> 25:14.290
I played at U.T. with Kyle --
but the other side of the ball.

25:15.225 --> 25:17.359
Manny Monroe --
"Manny the Man"!

25:17.394 --> 25:19.495
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ] A few years and whole lot

25:19.529 --> 25:21.096
of enchilada plates later.
Yeah, a whole lot.

25:21.131 --> 25:23.699
Yeah, Mr. Triathlete here
can eat as much as he wants.

25:23.733 --> 25:25.167
Well, I think you look great.

25:25.201 --> 25:26.835
So do you, as always.

25:26.870 --> 25:28.070
We need
to ask you some questions

25:28.104 --> 25:31.006
about your husband's crime.
Manny...

25:31.041 --> 25:32.441
You know Kyle.

25:32.475 --> 25:33.776
I mean,
he's not a bad guy.

25:33.810 --> 25:35.511
But I still need
to do my job.

25:35.545 --> 25:37.546
Okay. Ask away.

25:37.580 --> 25:39.048
Timeline --

25:39.082 --> 25:41.684
so, Kyle leaves
the family home last year,

25:41.718 --> 25:44.353
spends some time
south of the border,

25:44.387 --> 25:46.288
comes back to get some
construction work in the states.

25:46.323 --> 25:48.524
Sounds about right,
as far as I know it.

25:48.558 --> 25:50.059
Did Mr. Parks
ever give you any funds

25:50.093 --> 25:51.694
off the sale
from the stolen copper wire?

25:51.728 --> 25:53.688
Is this one of those
trick questions? [ Chuckles ]

25:56.499 --> 25:57.800
No.

25:57.834 --> 26:00.369
No one has given me
any money.

26:00.403 --> 26:03.072
Really? You know,
'cause I can't help notice

26:03.106 --> 26:04.807
you got a really nice
outfit there.

26:04.841 --> 26:08.510
Manny the man here might be
your friend, but I'm not.

26:09.846 --> 26:11.246
I'll be watching you.

26:12.582 --> 26:14.950
Well, I'll try to give y'all
something good to look at.

26:24.594 --> 26:26.762
Hey.
Travis, what's wrong?

26:26.796 --> 26:28.731
Samantha's mom told me

26:28.765 --> 26:30.799
I couldn't go
to the pizza party.

26:34.437 --> 26:36.739
Oh, she did, did she?

26:36.773 --> 26:38.073
I'll be right back.

26:38.108 --> 26:39.475
[ Indistinct conversation ]

26:41.378 --> 26:42.911
[ Laughing ] I know.
That family.

26:42.946 --> 26:44.079
Hey.

26:44.114 --> 26:45.414
You still sober?

26:45.448 --> 26:47.316
Your nose job looks great.
[ Chuckles ]

26:48.618 --> 26:51.253
You know, I remember
taking care of both of your kids

26:51.287 --> 26:52.988
when you guys
were having some problems.

26:54.124 --> 26:55.691
You know,
I paid $22.50

26:55.725 --> 26:57.760
for Travis to be able
to go to this pizza party,

26:57.794 --> 27:00.329
so he's gonna
see y'all later, right?

27:01.798 --> 27:03.699
That's what I thought.

27:03.733 --> 27:05.100
Look, you can say
whatever you want

27:05.135 --> 27:06.602
about me
and my husband,

27:06.636 --> 27:09.204
but don't take it out
on an innocent child.

27:09.239 --> 27:12.007
It's just not ladylike.

27:13.743 --> 27:15.110
Who wants pizza?

27:15.145 --> 27:16.178
Me! Me!

27:16.212 --> 27:18.013
Whoo! Let's go.
Come on.

27:19.082 --> 27:20.682
Ladies.

27:25.597 --> 27:27.065
Thanks
for squeezing me in.

27:27.099 --> 27:29.200
Of course. It was nice
to see you last night.

27:29.234 --> 27:32.136
It was also nice
to see you tell them off.

27:32.171 --> 27:34.238
I wouldn't have
had the courage.

27:34.273 --> 27:37.075
So, how can I
help you today?

27:37.109 --> 27:39.711
Well, uh, I need to open
a small line of credit

27:39.745 --> 27:40.745
on my house

27:40.779 --> 27:41.813
for some attorney fees.

27:41.847 --> 27:43.281
I understand.

27:43.315 --> 27:46.050
Riley, are you sure you want
to take on more debt?

27:46.085 --> 27:48.219
Is there anyone
you can borrow the money from?

27:48.253 --> 27:50.054
Any chance
of taking on extra work?

27:50.089 --> 27:52.423
I don't know anybody
that has that kind of cash,

27:52.458 --> 27:54.192
and...as far
as more income --

27:56.095 --> 27:58.563
look, the thing is,
I need the money right now

27:58.597 --> 27:59.764
for the retainer.

27:59.798 --> 28:01.432
Okay. Let's see.

28:01.467 --> 28:02.667
[ Keyboard clacks ]

28:02.701 --> 28:04.736
Well, you've got
some equity,

28:04.770 --> 28:06.437
so that
should be fine,

28:06.472 --> 28:10.241
but I see you've made
some large deposits in cash.

28:10.275 --> 28:12.910
I'm a manager
at the spa,

28:12.945 --> 28:16.080
and so...I get tips
on the massages that I give.

28:16.115 --> 28:17.248
I get it,

28:17.282 --> 28:18.750
but you know
how the IRS is.

28:18.784 --> 28:20.985
They go after
the most hard-working people.

28:21.787 --> 28:23.254
After we pull
this line of credit,

28:23.288 --> 28:24.522
we'll figure it out.

28:24.556 --> 28:26.791
[ Sighs ]
I really appreciate it.

28:26.825 --> 28:29.193
We single moms
got to stick together.

28:29.228 --> 28:30.828
[ Laughs ]

28:36.402 --> 28:38.703
Let me guess.
[ Sighs ]

28:38.737 --> 28:39.804
Parks family grapevine?

28:39.838 --> 28:42.140
Better than GPS tracking.

28:42.174 --> 28:44.108
So, did you forget something
last night?

28:44.143 --> 28:47.044
Evan -- to call you.
I'm so sorry. [ Sighs ]

28:47.079 --> 28:48.146
It's okay.

28:49.348 --> 28:51.315
Protein. Hydration.
[ Laughs ]

28:53.252 --> 28:54.952
Look, I know you got
a lot going on.

28:54.987 --> 28:58.122
Don't you think we deserve
a little selfish time?

28:58.157 --> 28:59.724
Come on, then.

28:59.758 --> 29:01.325
Spend some selfish time
with me?

29:03.996 --> 29:05.496
Come on!

29:05.531 --> 29:07.265
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

29:07.299 --> 29:09.867
[ Chuckling ] So, after
the papier-mâché fell apart,

29:09.902 --> 29:12.437
we had to put the whole
darn thing back together again

29:12.471 --> 29:14.639
using pasta
and a balloon.

29:15.808 --> 29:17.475
Who knew the intestines
could be so fascinating?

29:17.509 --> 29:18.976
[ Laughs ]

29:19.011 --> 29:20.778
Go with your gut --
that's what I always say.

29:20.813 --> 29:21.879
Couldn't agree
with you more.

29:21.914 --> 29:23.114
[ Laughs ]

29:23.148 --> 29:24.315
Oh.

29:24.349 --> 29:25.817
Do you remember
senior year

29:25.851 --> 29:27.452
when we found ourselves
out here all alone?

29:27.486 --> 29:29.454
You mean when you dropped
your purse in the stands here

29:29.488 --> 29:31.956
and everything spilled out?
Of course I remember. [ Laughs ]

29:31.990 --> 29:34.492
Hours and hours spent crawling
around on our hands and knees.

29:34.526 --> 29:35.660
Like a couple
of lunatics.

29:35.694 --> 29:37.061
Yeah,
we did find everything.

29:37.095 --> 29:38.362
No, we did not.

29:38.397 --> 29:39.564
We never found
my lucky lip gloss.

29:39.598 --> 29:41.132
Okay. I still
don't understand that.

29:41.166 --> 29:42.366
How can lip gloss
be lucky?

29:42.401 --> 29:43.835
You're never gonna
understand it.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.636
It's a girl thing.

29:45.671 --> 29:48.306
Well, it did get us
alone together in the stadium,

29:48.340 --> 29:50.675
so maybe it was lucky.
Evan, put that down.

29:50.709 --> 29:52.009
Oh, no.
What do we got here?

29:52.044 --> 29:54.078
We got a brush,
we got a cellphone,

29:54.112 --> 29:56.347
but where's
that lucky lip gloss?

29:58.283 --> 30:00.051
Well,
that's right here.

30:01.687 --> 30:03.087
Are you sure
that's the lucky one?

30:03.121 --> 30:04.388
Only one way
to find out.

30:04.423 --> 30:06.324
♪ I will meet you
down the line ♪

30:06.358 --> 30:07.658
[ Cellphone rings ]

30:07.693 --> 30:08.659
[ Groans ]

30:08.694 --> 30:10.528
Give me that.

30:10.562 --> 30:11.829
[ Cellphone beeps ]

30:11.864 --> 30:13.397
Hello.

30:14.700 --> 30:16.167
Uh, sure.

30:16.201 --> 30:18.503
Yeah, I'll be there
as soon as I can.

30:18.537 --> 30:19.871
Thank you.

30:19.905 --> 30:21.172
[ Cellphone beeps ]
[ Clears throat ]

30:21.206 --> 30:22.707
That was, uh,
Kyle's attorney.

30:23.976 --> 30:25.009
Kyle.

30:25.043 --> 30:26.210
Yeah, I got to go.

30:26.245 --> 30:29.013
♪ I'll meet you down the line

30:29.047 --> 30:32.650
♪ I will meet you
down the line ♪

30:35.053 --> 30:36.387
[ Sighs ]

30:38.257 --> 30:40.124
I got your call.
What's the emergency?

30:40.158 --> 30:42.026
You need to talk some sense
into your husband.

30:42.060 --> 30:43.060
What's going on?

30:43.996 --> 30:45.396
I told you
to leave her out of this.

30:45.397 --> 30:46.797
She hired me
to get you out,

30:46.832 --> 30:48.533
and this is
the only way, all right?

30:48.567 --> 30:49.901
You have to give up
your accomplice.

30:49.935 --> 30:52.036
Yeah, and I told you
that I can't.

30:52.070 --> 30:55.206
Kyle, if it's the only way
to get you out, start talking.

30:55.240 --> 30:58.309
Look, I know that it seems
crazy, but I have my reasons.

30:58.343 --> 30:59.810
You just have to trust me.

30:59.845 --> 31:01.212
Are you kidding me?

31:01.246 --> 31:03.381
You've got
two kids at home.

31:03.415 --> 31:05.550
You're gonna be
a stand-up guy for some crook?

31:05.584 --> 31:07.718
Why don't you be
a stand-up guy for them?

31:07.753 --> 31:11.756
The longer we wait, the harder
it'll be to cut a deal.

31:17.629 --> 31:20.231
I'm sorry. Talking was
never our strong suit.

31:20.265 --> 31:21.265
Riley,
don't walk out like that.

31:21.300 --> 31:23.434
Like you walked out
on me?

31:24.937 --> 31:28.439
Do not call me again until
he's got something to say.

31:38.283 --> 31:40.618
[ Sniffles ]

31:48.493 --> 31:50.561
[ Sniffles ]

31:52.331 --> 31:53.431
[ Sniffles ]

31:53.465 --> 31:54.966
Oh, lord.

31:55.000 --> 31:56.801
[ Sniffles ]

31:56.835 --> 31:59.103
[ Sighs ]

31:59.137 --> 32:00.438
[ Laughs ]

32:00.472 --> 32:02.273
[ Door closes ]

32:02.307 --> 32:05.142
Oh, hey, hey.
Hey, hold up.

32:05.177 --> 32:07.311
So, Mr. Louboutin
brought in a friend.

32:07.346 --> 32:09.780
You must have blown
his socks off yesterday.

32:09.815 --> 32:11.949
Oh, lord. Please don't give
that many any new ideas.

32:11.984 --> 32:13.384
[ Laughs ]
Is he waiting on me?

32:13.418 --> 32:14.385
Yeah, in reception.

32:14.419 --> 32:15.786
You know, honey,

32:15.821 --> 32:17.788
your -- your eyes are
looking a little swell,

32:17.823 --> 32:19.457
and I don't mean that
in a good way.

32:19.491 --> 32:21.459
Didn't think you would.
Must be my allergies.

32:21.493 --> 32:23.294
You should see me
when I have hay fever.

32:23.328 --> 32:24.829
Here. Try that.

32:24.863 --> 32:26.297
Thank you.

32:26.331 --> 32:27.465
Sure.

32:27.499 --> 32:29.300
Like you said,
us Rub girls,

32:29.334 --> 32:31.335
we got to stick together,
right?

32:31.370 --> 32:33.337
Yeah.

32:33.372 --> 32:34.572
I said that.

32:34.606 --> 32:35.673
Right.

32:40.379 --> 32:42.680
I was raving
to my friend Clyde here

32:42.714 --> 32:45.683
about that amazing massage
you gave me yesterday.

32:45.717 --> 32:47.652
Oh. So, you want a tour?
Okay.

32:47.686 --> 32:50.021
Well, then,
let's start in my office.

32:51.056 --> 32:53.858
There's a lot
of special things we offer.

32:53.892 --> 32:55.159
Have a seat.

32:55.193 --> 32:58.162
And we have
a lot of special girls.

32:58.196 --> 33:02.667
Okay, so...you want to be
on the client list.

33:02.701 --> 33:04.835
Well, that's...great.

33:04.870 --> 33:06.170
Here's how it works.

33:06.204 --> 33:08.039
If we accept you
onto the list

33:08.073 --> 33:10.441
and you betray the Rub
in any way,

33:10.475 --> 33:12.710
the guy that brought you here
is responsible.

33:12.744 --> 33:14.779
You take us down,
you take him down --

33:14.813 --> 33:15.780
we all go down.

33:15.814 --> 33:17.181
Like dominoes.

33:17.215 --> 33:18.536
It's how we keep
ourselves safe --

33:18.550 --> 33:21.185
me, the girls,
the clients, everyone.

33:21.219 --> 33:23.621
Now, whatever you
and the girl decide,

33:23.655 --> 33:27.892
totally up to you, as long
as it is 100% consensual.

33:27.926 --> 33:29.560
And the owner of the Rub
gets a cut of everything.

33:29.594 --> 33:30.961
Oh, and there's
one more rule.

33:30.996 --> 33:34.031
It's kind of like, um --
like the "Fight Club."

33:34.066 --> 33:37.468
We don't talk about,
and we don't mention the list

33:37.502 --> 33:39.370
anywhere outside this room.

33:39.404 --> 33:41.539
There are many powerful
individuals on that list --

33:41.573 --> 33:43.040
or so I've heard.

33:43.075 --> 33:45.042
Yeah, and you're never gonna
find out who they are

33:45.077 --> 33:46.577
'cause it is
completely confidential.

33:46.611 --> 33:48.145
And I promise you,

33:48.180 --> 33:50.715
they will crush
whoever violates those rules.

33:50.749 --> 33:52.383
Who controls the list?

33:52.417 --> 33:55.386
I'm the manager,
so I call the shots.

33:55.420 --> 33:56.554
What about Georgia?

33:56.588 --> 33:57.755
I'm gonna be taking over

33:57.789 --> 34:00.091
more of her
responsibilities.

34:00.125 --> 34:02.426
Now,
you have any questions?

34:02.461 --> 34:03.427
Just one.

34:03.462 --> 34:05.329
When can I start?

34:05.363 --> 34:07.865
[ Chuckles ]

34:13.638 --> 34:15.438
Hey.
Nice necklace.

34:15.474 --> 34:16.507
Oh.

34:16.541 --> 34:18.576
Yeah,
thanks for the referral.

34:18.610 --> 34:20.745
That new guy, Clyde,
loves pearls.

34:20.779 --> 34:22.413
A pearl necklace.

34:22.447 --> 34:23.447
Really?

34:25.150 --> 34:26.449
Okay.

34:26.485 --> 34:29.253
[ Laughs ]

34:29.286 --> 34:31.755
Ew.

34:31.790 --> 34:35.458
Kyle Parks,
your visitor's here.

34:39.797 --> 34:42.433
[ Sighs ]

34:42.467 --> 34:44.201
What the hell
are you thinking?

34:44.235 --> 34:45.536
You know, the last thing
I need right now

34:45.570 --> 34:46.771
is a lecture from you.

34:46.804 --> 34:48.472
Riley was just getting
on her feet.

34:48.507 --> 34:49.940
Kids were doing great.

34:49.975 --> 34:51.775
You come back here,
bring nothing but trouble.

34:51.810 --> 34:54.043
I came home
for my family.

34:54.079 --> 34:55.799
Yeah, they were doing
just fine without you.

34:55.813 --> 34:57.381
You know, you should've
just stayed gone.

34:57.415 --> 34:58.736
And you should stop
standing there

34:58.750 --> 35:00.151
acting like you're
some kind of hero

35:00.185 --> 35:01.719
when you're off sneaking around
behind my back.

35:01.753 --> 35:04.622
You got something
to say to me?

35:04.656 --> 35:05.790
Yeah, I do.

35:05.824 --> 35:08.692
I saw you with my wife.

35:10.028 --> 35:12.329
Riley needs me.

35:12.364 --> 35:14.632
You know,
I've been there for her --

35:14.666 --> 35:16.801
after you abandoned
your family.

35:16.835 --> 35:18.202
Right.

35:18.236 --> 35:20.004
And there was nothing in it
for you, right?

35:21.439 --> 35:23.941
What kind of man takes advantage
of his brother's wife?

35:26.178 --> 35:27.845
You never did have the balls
to go out

35:27.879 --> 35:29.647
and make a life of your own,
did you?

35:29.681 --> 35:30.781
[ Grunts ]

35:43.195 --> 35:45.496
All right, all right, all right,
all right, all right!

35:45.530 --> 35:47.198
You should have
stayed gone, Kyle!

35:47.232 --> 35:49.500
You should have
stayed gone!

36:05.353 --> 36:08.255
Seriously?

36:12.157 --> 36:13.557
[ Sighs ]

36:13.591 --> 36:15.111
Well, at least Kyle
left you something.

36:15.453 --> 36:17.087
My window's being fixed.

36:17.121 --> 36:19.256
I figured he wasn't gonna need
his truck for a while.

36:19.290 --> 36:20.424
Well, it suits you.

36:20.458 --> 36:22.059
Thanks for coming to get me.

36:22.093 --> 36:23.760
I had no idea what I was
supposed to tell the kids --

36:23.795 --> 36:25.262
that both their daddy
and Uncle are in jail.

36:25.296 --> 36:27.564
Do the kids know where Kyle is?
No.

36:27.599 --> 36:29.433
I wanted to wait
until after the arraignment.

36:29.467 --> 36:31.068
Hopefully they'll
never have to know.

36:31.102 --> 36:33.136
That's probably a good idea.
They've been through enough.

36:33.171 --> 36:35.239
Got to protect them
as long as you can.

36:35.273 --> 36:37.574
You know, are you gonnatell me
what you two were fighting about,

36:37.609 --> 36:38.895
or are we just gonna keep
dancing around it?

36:38.896 --> 36:39.470
We're brothers,
all right?

36:39.472 --> 36:40.977
We got a lot of history,
and we're both hot-headed.

36:40.978 --> 36:42.079
[ Sighs ] Oh, yeah.

36:42.113 --> 36:43.747
Riley, don't you see?

36:43.781 --> 36:45.449
You could leave Kyle right now,
and nobody would blame you.

36:45.483 --> 36:47.251
Travis and Katie would.

36:47.285 --> 36:50.387
They would never forgive me.

36:50.421 --> 36:52.422
Look, Evan, I told you
that I can't just walk away,

36:52.457 --> 36:53.891
and if you don't
understand that,

36:53.925 --> 36:55.592
then I don't know
what we're doing here.

36:59.430 --> 37:01.665
Buddy, you're wasting my time.
Why am I here?

37:01.699 --> 37:03.066
You already made it clear

37:03.101 --> 37:04.568
that you won't give up
your accomplice.

37:04.602 --> 37:06.069
I have made
my share of mistakes,

37:06.104 --> 37:07.905
but I am not gonna lose my wife
because of them.

37:07.939 --> 37:09.506
All right, well,
I'm glad to hear that.

37:09.541 --> 37:11.074
And, so, the name
of your accomplice?

37:11.109 --> 37:12.509
I'm still not
giving that up.

37:13.778 --> 37:15.546
But there is something else
that could help.

37:17.282 --> 37:20.117
Some things that would mean
a lot more to a prosecutor

37:20.151 --> 37:23.220
than just some copper wire.

37:34.666 --> 37:36.934
Interesting place.

37:36.968 --> 37:38.936
Oh.
It belongs to Harold.

37:38.970 --> 37:41.939
He's redoing it,
but it's gonna be cute.

37:41.973 --> 37:44.274
I think I have a solution
to your problem.

37:44.309 --> 37:46.043
With Harold?
Go on.

37:46.077 --> 37:48.779
Okay, so, you don't want to lie
to the man that you love,

37:48.813 --> 37:51.782
but you can't let go
of the spa.

37:51.816 --> 37:53.650
Because you girls need me.
Right.

37:53.685 --> 37:56.286
But what if you helped us
with what we needed,

37:56.321 --> 37:58.789
but you weren't tied
to anything on paper.

37:58.823 --> 38:01.291
Riley,
what are you getting at?

38:01.326 --> 38:04.294
Well, I think
you should sell it...

38:04.329 --> 38:06.463
to someone that you trust,
somebody who knows the business.

38:06.497 --> 38:09.666
Honey,
you are not suggesting --

38:09.701 --> 38:11.969
My bills are piling up.

38:12.003 --> 38:13.403
And with attorney fees,

38:13.438 --> 38:15.339
I just don't know
that I'm gonna make it.

38:15.373 --> 38:16.673
But if I was the owner --

38:16.708 --> 38:17.975
Oh, but...

38:18.009 --> 38:20.177
There would be
so much more risk.

38:20.211 --> 38:22.479
Look, I'll be
as careful as I can,

38:22.513 --> 38:24.147
but honestly...
[ Sighs ]

38:24.182 --> 38:26.083
...it's a risk
I just might have to take.

38:26.117 --> 38:31.355
You would no longer have to lie
to the man that you love.

38:31.389 --> 38:33.857
And no more secret life.

38:35.393 --> 38:36.860
Think about it.

38:43.368 --> 38:45.402
[ Door opens ]

38:47.805 --> 38:49.773
What are those for?

38:49.807 --> 38:52.275
For being stupid.

38:52.310 --> 38:55.679
For thinking of myself
and not you and the kids.

38:55.713 --> 38:56.847
Oh.

38:56.881 --> 38:58.115
It's been hard
on all of us.

38:58.149 --> 38:59.883
I know it's not fair
to ask you to wait.

38:59.917 --> 39:02.853
But it's what we got to do.

39:02.887 --> 39:05.522
Until things with Kyle
get sorted out,

39:05.556 --> 39:08.859
I'll take what I can get.

39:08.893 --> 39:11.728
I'd regret it for the rest
of my life if I didn't.

39:11.763 --> 39:13.430
[ Sighs ]

39:17.235 --> 39:19.069
Katie: Mommy!

39:19.103 --> 39:20.737
Travis:
Mommy, is that you?

39:20.772 --> 39:23.073
Uncle Evan,
you're eating dinner with us?

39:23.107 --> 39:24.374
Uh, yeah.

39:24.409 --> 39:26.143
Uh, I was thinking
of, uh, making

39:26.177 --> 39:28.712
Uncle Evan's
famous burgers and shakes.

39:28.746 --> 39:31.048
Great! Yay!

39:31.082 --> 39:33.817
Ooh, you know what would
make it even better?

39:33.851 --> 39:35.585
If daddy
was here with us.

39:35.620 --> 39:37.688
[ Neko Case's
"Wish I Was the Moon" plays ]

39:41.025 --> 39:45.228
♪ God blessed me,
I'm a free man ♪

39:45.263 --> 39:49.566
♪ with no place free to go

39:49.600 --> 39:53.737
♪ paralyzed and collar tight

39:53.771 --> 39:57.274
♪ no pills for what I fear

39:57.308 --> 40:00.577
♪ this is crazy

40:00.611 --> 40:05.115
♪ I wish I was
the moon tonight ♪

40:06.818 --> 40:11.121
♪ chimney falls
as lovers blaze ♪

40:11.155 --> 40:14.791
♪ I thought that I was young

40:14.826 --> 40:19.463
♪ now I've freezing hands
and bloodless veins ♪

40:19.497 --> 40:22.933
♪ as numb as I've become

40:22.967 --> 40:24.768
♪ I'm so tired

40:24.802 --> 40:26.103
[ cellphone ringing ]

40:26.137 --> 40:30.707
♪ I wish I was
the moon tonight ♪

40:30.742 --> 40:32.442
[ Ringing ]

40:32.477 --> 40:35.145
[ Cellphone ringing, beeps ]

40:35.179 --> 40:36.480
Hey, Georgia.

40:36.514 --> 40:39.583
I've been thinking --
your proposal.

40:41.018 --> 40:43.153
I'm selling you the spa.

40:44.522 --> 40:46.490
Okay.

40:46.524 --> 40:47.791
It's a deal.

40:47.825 --> 40:50.327
Deal.

40:50.361 --> 40:51.795
[ Cellphone beeps ]

40:51.829 --> 40:54.998
So, you're finally
passing the baton.

40:55.032 --> 40:56.633
Hello, Judge.

40:56.667 --> 40:59.970
After 20 years in the business,
it was time to move on.

41:00.004 --> 41:02.906
After that nasty business
with the councilman.

41:02.940 --> 41:05.976
I do appreciate you
getting him off our backs.

41:06.010 --> 41:07.310
Long as I can
get off on mine.

41:07.345 --> 41:08.311
[ Laughs ]

41:08.346 --> 41:11.181
Oh, you are a powerful man.

41:11.215 --> 41:12.849
Indeed, I am.

41:12.884 --> 41:17.287
However, there are limits
to my reach.

41:19.357 --> 41:21.525
A request
for a search warrant?

41:21.559 --> 41:24.494
Now, I'm stalling the
authorities as long as I can,

41:24.529 --> 41:26.530
but I'm not sure
how much longer

41:26.564 --> 41:28.532
I can keep them
away from her.

